          "text": " is a multi-statement table-valued function in Microsoft SQL Server. This type of function allows for complex logic to be executed and returns a table as a result. The function is designed to calculate and return billing periods based on the input parameters provided. It involves multiple steps or iterations to construct the final result set, which is why it is implemented as a multi-statement function."
